<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="1057" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1057">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115W31.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of the Navy</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-10">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 10, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to enclose herewith a
                            copy of a telegram, dated April 9, which the Department despatched to
                            the American <pb facs="0786" n="670" xml:id="pg_670"/> Consul at
                            Tampico, Mexico, in regard to the protection of the extensive foreign
                            oil interests in the vicinity of Tampico. This important telegram is
                            transmitted for your information as it reflects this Department’s
                            attitude.</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to request that the Secretary of the Navy issue to the
                            Admiral in command of the Gulf Fleet an appropriate instruction in
                            conformity with the telegram which was sent by this Department last
                            night to the American Consul at Tampico.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>